A considerable variability has been found to occur in all studied populations. The shape of lateral pronotal borders turned out to be particularly variable, while the form of pronotal sculpture ranges from largely areolaterugose (
Fig. 21
) to completely rugose (
Fig. 27
), often with only hints of polygonal cells (
Fig. 23
). An extreme variability in the size of the aedeagus has also been verified in males, regardless of locality, and even in specimens obtained from single host-plant samples ( teste Bílý and Kubáň). These morphological characters are those used by the various authors in the differentiation of the above-mentioned species. With regard to the dorsal colouration, there is great variability even among specimens obtained from the same wood sample.
